<div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-12">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Good Faith</h1>

  <div class="prose lg:prose-xl max-w-4xl">
    <p class="mb-4">We expect questions to be asked <strong>in good faith</strong>. If they are, we don't require you to get everything right.
    <p>

    <p class="mb-4">Genderbase is a place you can get answers from people who have signed up to deal with potentially offensive language, as long as it's accidental. You can't be expected to get everything right without help, and we want you to use us to get that help without worry of upsetting anyone.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">What Does "Good Faith" Mean?</h2>

    <p class="mb-4"><strong>Our expectations of you:</strong> Questions should be asked with genuine curiosity and a sincere desire to learn and understand. Approach conversations with respect, honesty, and an openness to receiving new information — even when that information might challenge your existing beliefs.</p>

    <p class="mb-4"><strong>What we offer in return:</strong> We will not respond with hostility to questions that may be posed in an offensive way, and will aim to give you the best answer we can. We will correct any missteps, but we will treat you with the same respect which you show us.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">What's Allowed Under Our Good Faith Policy</h2>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6">
      <li class="mb-2"><strong>Imperfect language:</strong> Using outdated, incorrect, or offensive terminology when it's sincerely accidental or based on a lack of knowledge.</li>
      <li class="mb-2"><strong>Challenging:</strong> If you disagree with something the responder has said, you can raise it for further discussion. This is something that risks straying into disallowed territory, but if you keep things respectful, it doesn't inherently break the policy.</li>
      <li class="mb-2"><strong>Basic questions:</strong> Asking fundamental questions about gender concepts that might seem obvious to others but are new to you.</li>
      <li class="mb-2"><strong>Clarification requests:</strong> Asking for explanations when you don't understand something raised in the answer. You are able to have an ongoing conversation with your responder.</li>
      <li class="mb-2"><strong>Respectful disagreement:</strong> Expressing confusion or requesting evidence while remaining open to learning.</li>
      <li class="mb-2"><strong>Personal experience questions:</strong> Asking about lived experiences, in a respectful way. The lived experience of the responder can be useful.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">What's Not Allowed</h2>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6">
      <li class="mb-2"><strong>Trolling:</strong> Deliberately asking provocative questions designed to upset or anger others.</li>
      <li class="mb-2"><strong>Sealioning:</strong> Asking questions in a way that appears civil but is actually intended to harass or waste time.</li>
      <li class="mb-2"><strong>Debating identity:</strong> Challenging your responder's gender identity.</li>
      <li class="mb-2"><strong>Repeated violations:</strong> Continuing to use harmful language after being corrected.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">If Your Question Is Closed</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">If your question is closed due to violation of this policy, you will be able to appeal <strong>once</strong>. Responders will evaluate your appeal and if it is accepted, your question will be reopened. You may be assigned a new responder.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">How We Evaluate Good Faith</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">Our responders consider several factors when determining if a question is asked in good faith, including but not limited to &mdash;</p>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6">
      <li class="mb-2">The language and tone of the question.</li>
      <li class="mb-2">Whether the person engages respectfully with answers and corrections.</li>
      <li class="mb-2">Willingness to learn and adjust language when informed.</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="mb-4">We reserve the right to close questions that are not asked in good faith without answering. Our responders are human and do not deserve to be harassed.</p>

    <p class="mb-4">Our goal is to maintain Genderbase as a space where people can learn about gender identity and expression without fear, while ensuring the community remains respectful and supportive.</p>

    <div class="mt-8">
      <%= link_to "About Genderbase", home_about_path, class: "btn btn-primary mr-4" %>
      <%= link_to "Help & Support", home_support_path, class: "btn btn-outline" %>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>